mission.name: Delta IV - NROL-45
mission.mission: The mission will be launched for the National Reconnaissance Office in support of national defense.

launch_site: Space Launch Complex (SLC)-6 at Vandenberg Air Force Base, California
notes: NROL-45 will be the 31st Delta IV mission since the vehicle’s inaugural launch in 2002, and the 9th NRO mission to launch on Delta IV.

feed.name: T-5 minutes, 0 seconds
feed.description: Start auxiliary power units.

feed.name: T-3 minutes, 55 seconds
feed.description: Start orbiter aerosurface profile test, followed by main engine gimbal profile test

feed.name: T-3 minutes, 20 seconds
feed.description: CBC liquid hydrogen and liquid oxygen tank secured. Propellant fill and drain valves closed.

feed.name: T-3 minutes
feed.description: Vehicle ordinance system armed. Booster liquid oxygen and liquid hydrogen propellant tanks verified and at flight pressure and flight level.

feed.name: T-2 minutes, 0 seconds
feed.description: Hydraulic system pressure verified. Booster, DCSS and flight termination system battery voltages are confirmed.

feed.name: T-1 minute, 20 seconds
feed.description: Securing second stage liquid hydrogen tank.

feed.name: T-50 seconds
feed.description: Orbiter transfers from ground to internal power

feed.name: T-31 seconds
feed.description: Ground launch sequencer is go for auto sequence start

feed.name: T-25 seconds
feed.description: Launch vehicle and spacecraft status check complete.

feed.name: T-9 minutes and counting
feed.description: Start automatic ground launch sequencer.

feed.name: T-7 minutes, 30 seconds
feed.description: Retract orbiter access arm.

feed.name: T-5 minutes, 0 seconds
feed.description: Arm solid rocket booster range safety safe and arm devices

feed.name: T-4 minutes and counting
feed.description: Entering the terminal count and second stage liquid oxygen tank is secure.

feed.name: T-3 minutes, 32 seconds
feed.description: Transfer from ground facility power to internal battery power complete.

feed.name: T-2 minutes, 55 seconds
feed.description: Retract gaseous oxygen vent arm, or "beanie cap"

feed.name: T-2 minutes, 0 seconds
feed.description: Crew members close and lock their visors

feed.name: T-60 seconds
feed.description: Western range readiness verified.

feed.name: T-50 seconds
feed.description: DCSS liquid hydrogen tank is secured a flight level.

feed.name: T-16 seconds
feed.description: Activate launch pad sound suppression system

feed.name: T-15 seconds
feed.description: Radial Outward Firing Igniters (ROFIs, or “sparklers”) are guided to burn off excess hydrogen at the base of the vehicle.

feed.name: T-10 seconds
feed.description: Activate main engine hydrogen burnoff system

feed.name: T-6.6 seconds
feed.description: Main engine start

feed.name: T-0
feed.description: Solid rocket booster ignition and liftoff
